  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Glow]]></title>
    <link href="http://adamsaewitz.github.io/glow/"/>
    <updated>2014-01-20T18:29:57-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://adamsaewitz.github.io/glow</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="embed-video-container"><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/QXW69VAeCvI "></iframe></div>


<p>I met Dominic who runs <a href="http://thisisluckyme.com/">LuckyMe</a> sometime around 2010. We both connected over our mutual admiration for <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xAHphpMC9zg">Clipse</a> and shortly afterwards he approached me to direct Lunice’s first music video. I knew I wanted to incorporate Lunice&rsquo;s <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JX_sx9Rr710">b-boy background</a> I took incense and a video-projector into my closet. I projected my iTunes visualizer against the incense smoke to create a glowing palette. With my DSLR I photographed the projector light striking the incense. In post, I composited Lunice dancing directly on top of my glowing images. I believe I used a hard-light filter in Final Cut so the smoke seamlessly blended into Lunice’s body.</p>
]]></content>
